ring of adornment
	Modifies your charisma. The change in charisma is equal to the
	ring's enchantment; the enchantment can be altered by charging.
	Succubi will steal or ask for rings of adornment.
ring of gain constitution
	Modifies your constitution. The change in constituion is equal
	to the ring's enchantment; the enchantment can be altered by
	charging. The boost to constitution exceeds racial limitations
	up to a maximum of 25.
ring of gain dexterity
	 Modifies your dexterity. The change in dexterity is equal to the
	 ring's enchantment; the enchantment can be altered by charging.
ring of gain intelligence
	 Modifies your intelligence. The change in intelligence is equal
	 to the ring's enchantment; the enchantment can be altered by
	 charging.
ring of gain strength
	A ring of gain strength increases your strength by its enchantment,
	which can be altered by charging. At 18 strength, the ring will
	instead increase percentile dice by its enchantment.
ring of gain wisdom
	A ring of gain wisdom increases your wisdom by its enchantment,
	which can be altered by charging.
ring of increase accuracy
	A ring of increase accuracy adds its enchantment to your to-hit
	rolls. The enchantment can be altered by charging. Like the ring
	of increase damage, it can be eaten for a chance at obtaining an
	intrinsic accuracy bonus provided it is of an edible material.
ring of increase damage
	A ring of increase damage adds its enchantment to your damage
	rolls. The enchantment can be altered by charging. This does not
	affect damage you deal with spells. The effect stacks if you wear
	two of them.
	If the ring is of an edible material, it may be possible to eat it
	to permanently gain a damage bonus.
ring of protection
	A ring of protection also increases your magic cancellation by 1,
	to a maximum of 3. This does not depend on its enchantment, and
	it does not stack with a second ring of protection.
	The enchantment can be altered by charging.

	Eating a ring of protection with non-zero enchantment has a chance
	of conferring intrinsic protection.
ring of regeneration
	While wearing it, you heal more quickly. While you are healing you
	will burn more nutrition, but when at full health the ring will
	stop using up nutrition.
	Regeneration causes you to heal one HP on any turn you would
	otherwise heal none. Regeneration is not cumulative, so wearing
	two such rings, or a ring along with another regeneration source,
	grants no further benefit.
ring of searching
	Grants you the automatic searching extrinsic, which automatically
	searches the squares around you at the end of each turn.

	Eating a ring of searching can give the automatic searching
	intrinsic.
ring of stealth
	Wearing a ring of stealth gives you extrinsic stealth.

	Polymorphing and eating the ring may grant you stealth as an
	intrinsic.
ring of sustain ability
	When worn, it prevents the wearer's base attributes from being
	changed in any way, except by polymorphing into your own race.
	This includes stat increase through exercise, as well as stat
	loss from abuse.
ring of levitation
	Wearing a ring of levitation causes you to levitate.
	While you are levitating, you will float over some otherwise
	hazardous terrain and traps, but you will not be able to touch
	the ground to pick up items.

	Levitating over a sink removes any sources of levitation and
	causes you to crash to the ground; this can be useful in removing
	a cursed ring of levitation, or a ring of levitation under cursed
	gloves.
ring of hunger
	Wearing a ring of hunger conveys the hunger extrinsic, which
	causes you to burn nutrition very quickly; every even-numbered
	turn your nutrition is decremented. It is usually generated
	cursed.
ring of aggravate monster
	Dropping a ring of hunger into a sink produces the message,
	"Suddenly, <item> vanishes from the sink!" but only if there's
	another item on the sink. This auto-identifies the ring.
	Otherwise, "You hear the ring bouncing down the drain pipe."
ring of conflict
	Wearing the ring will generate conflict, causing all monsters
	within line of sight and a radius of eight squares to attack the
	nearest monster, including you; monsters may resist this effect
	dependent on level and monster magic resistance. Every even-
	numbered turn you wear the ring, your nutrition is decremented by
	1.

	Conflict now takes the players charisma score into account. The
	formula is 'charisma - monster level + player level' and if that
	value is greater than 19, clamps it to be 19. There's then a
	percentage chance (rnd(20)) against the value generated on
	whether conflict kicks in or not. So even with charisma and your
	xp level maxed out, there's still a 5% chance of conflict not
	working. Also, the monsters affected have to see you for conflict
	to work.
ring of warning
	Wearing a ring of warning gives you the warning property. The
	warning will cause monsters to be displayed as numbers (or
	colored question marks, if playing with tiles). Warning is a
	valuable property to have; while it does not explicitly reveal
	the identity of the creatures a la telepathy, it has a larger
	range than telepathy, and works while unblind unlike intrinsic
	telepathy. Telepathy also does not sense mindless creatures like
	undead, whereas warning works on all but monsters of level 3 or
	lower. However, several roles get warning intrinsically as they
	increase in level; for them, a ring of warning is obviously
	useless once they reach that point.

	Wooden or metal rings of warning can be eaten to acquire warning
	intrinsically.
ring of poison resistance
	Wearing a ring of poison resistance conveys extrinsic poison
	resistance.
ring of fire resistance
	Wearing a ring of fire resistance conveys extrinsic fire
	resistance. This will also protect your items from fire
	destruction.
ring of cold resistance
	Wearing a ring of cold resistance conveys extrinsic cold
	resistance. This will also protect your items from cold damage.
ring of psychic resistance
	Wearing a ring of psychic resistance conveys extrinsic psychic
	resistance, which protects you from mental and fear attacks.

	This protect you from:
	- the negative effects of scrolls and potions of amnesia
	- Fear attacks (banshees, eye of fear and flame)
	- Being "paralyzed" by fear when an enormous ghost appears in a
	  deserted temple.
	- Dragon roars
	- Spell of psionic wave
ring of sonic resistance
	Wearing a ring of sonic resistance conveys extrinsic sonic
	resistance. This will also protect your items from sonic
	destruction. It is also immune to sonic damage.
ring of shock resistance
	Wearing a ring of shock resistance conveys extrinsic shock
	resistance. Unlike other rings, it is immune to electric damage
ring of free action
	Wearing a ring of free action gives you the free action extrinsic,
	which protects you from paralysis.

	Free action includes protection from:
    - Paralysis container traps
    - A thrown or quaffed potion of paralysis or potion of sleeping
    - Paralysis or stunning spells (reduced to one turn)

	In addition, protection from the paralyzing attacks of the following monsters:

	-Floating eyes passive attack
	-Gelatinous cubes, Ghouls, Guardian nagas, Shades, Yeenoghu, and others.

	Free action does not:
	- Protect you from being "paralyzed" by fear when an enormous
	  ghost appears in a deserted temple, or you chat to a skeleton
	- Protect you from sleep, except from potions of sleeping
	- Protect you from stunning, except from spells
	- Protect you from bear traps, pits, spider webs, or any
	  physically binding traps
	- Protect you from stoning
	- Allow you to move freely on the Plane of Air or Plane of Water
	- Prevent you from being incapacitated by lightning in clouds on
	  the Plane of Air
	- Grant any extra turns
	- Protect against helplessness caused by engraving, a cursed
	  spellbook, fumbling,[1] or hurtling through the air while
	  levitating.
	- Eating the ring will give you intrinsic sleep resistance
	  instead of free action.

	In Hack'EM, the ring does protect against grabbing attacks,
	including those of both drowning monsters and mind flayers, with
	a chance dependent on your Luck - 50% at 0 Luck, 90% when luck is
	maxed out.
ring of slow digestion
	When worn, the ring nullifies the ordinary consumption of one
	nutrition per turn. Nutrition consumption from all other sources,
	including the ring hunger from the ring itself, is unaffected;
	in practice, this means that a non-spellcasting player can go
	without being hungry twenty times longer than normal. Wearing
	two rings does not cause the effect to stack.

	If a monster attempts to engulf and digest you while you are
	wearing this ring, you will be expelled immediately (i.e. the
	ring slows your digestion).

	A cursed ring still has its effect.
ring of teleportation
	Wearing a ring of teleportation gives you teleportitis. These
	rings are often generated cursed.

	A cursed ring with a base price of 200 is very probably
	teleportation. To be sure, you can uncurse it and put it on -
	if ctrl + t gives "You cannot teleport at will" instead of
	"You don't know that spell", it is teleportation.

	The usefulness of teleportitis is rather schizophrenic;
	uncontrolled, it is usually considered a great annoyance, as you
	will often be teleported into danger (or worse, out of shops).
	Once the player gains teleport control, it is a great boon

	Dropping this ring down a sink will teleport the sink to a random
	location.
ring of teleport control
	Wearing a ring of teleport control conveys the teleport control
	extrinsic. This is an incredibly useful property, especially when
	combined with teleportitis or a means of level teleportation.
	Eating a ring of teleport control grants the property as an
	intrinsic.
ring of polymorph
	Wearing a ring of polymorph gives you polymorphitis, which has a
	1% chance of polymorphing you each turn. This ring is usually
	generated cursed, because uncontrolled polymorphitis can be
	frustrating. It can also cause system shock (unless you have
	control or are wearing dragon scales or dragon scale mail).

	If you have polymorph control, you may choose the form into which
	you polymorph. If you are inflicted with lycanthropy, the ring of
	polymorph will occasionally trigger a change into your normal
	form or the animal form of the werecreature that infected you.

	If you are wearing an amulet of unchanging, the ring of polymorph
	will have no effect (besides the usual ring hunger).

	Dropping the ring into a sink will polymorph the sink into one of
	altar, fountain, sink, grave, throne, or forge.
ring of polymorph control
	Grants polymorph control when worn. This allows you to choose what form you want to take when you polymorph.
	You will be asked "Become what type of monster? [type the name]".
	You can then choose to polymorph into a monster. Polymorph control
	will also allow you to decline a change in form brought upon by
	lycanthropy.

	Polymorphing into your own species will cause you to "feel like a
	new <species>!" and cause random change to your scores. There is a
	20% chance that this will happen in spite of polymorph control,
	even if a different monster is chosen.

	Polymorph control will not work if the player is stunned or
	unconscious. However, possessing polymorph control will always
	negate the possibility of system shock.

	Pay attention to the base level of the species, as this determines
	your resulting HP. If it is not enough to survive combat, you may
	need to increase it. This is only worthwhile if you plan to be
	unchanging, as the increase is lost when you transform back. You
	also regenerate HP at the same rate as your species, so having
	regeneration or healing magic is useful.

	When polymorphed into certain species, you can use their abilities
	with the #monster command:

	Females who polymorph into oviparous monsters can #sit to lay eggs,
	which hatch into pets of the same species.

	Most of your attributes are reset when you return to original form,
	but you keep any intrinsics gained while in monster form. For
	example, if you eat poisonous corpses that damage your strength,
	you may gain poison resistance and still keep your original
	strength when you change back.
