scroll of charging
    When read, this scroll can be used to charge wands, tools, or
    rings, or to increase your own magical energy.

	The scroll of charging, when read, prompts the player to choose
	an item to which a number of uses (or "charges") will be
	recharged. Blessed scrolls have a higher probability than
	uncursed scrolls to restore more charges on the item (and thus a
	higher chance to restore the maximum number of charges).

	- blessed: In addition to charging the item, also reveals the
	  number of charges and the charge counter.
    - cursed: Sets the number of charges on the item to zero and
      increments the charge counter by 1.

	Confused effects:
	- A noncursed scroll will instead increase your energy to the
	  maximum, unless your energy is already at maximum, in which
	  case your maximum energy will increase by 5-20 points.
	- If cursed, it will instead reduce your current energy to 0.

	Wands:
	- Blessed scrolls will always restore maximum charges to a
	  previously uncharged wand of wishing, and will always
	  restore any given directional wand to at least 4 charges or
	  any nondirectional wand other than wishing to 11 charges.
	  Specifically, a target charge count is determined; this is a
	  random number between the maximum charge count and 4 charges
	  fewer than that (4 to 8 for directional wands; 11 to 15
	  for nondirection wands other than wishing). Uncursed scrolls
	  do the same, but adjust the target charge count to a random
	  number from 1 to the original charge count. The wand then is
	  adjusted to that target charge count if it had fewer charges
	  previously. Otherwise, one charge is added. Wands can only be
	  recharged a certain number of times before the wand explodes,
	  dealing damage to you.
	- A specific change kept from EvilHack is that Wands of Death
	  can only be recharged once.

	Tools:
	- Except for a magic marker, which can only be recharged once,
	  all tools can be charged an unlimited number of times, with
	  varying amounts of charges recharged depending on the item.

	Rings:
	- All rings that have a numeric bonus on them (ie: ring of
	  adornment, can have their enchantment modified by the scroll
	  of charging. A blessed scroll adds between 1-3 points, an
	  uncursed scroll adds 1, and a cursed scroll decreases it by
	  1-2 points.
	- Rings have a chance of being destroyed if the enchantment is
	  too high or too low:

	Current enchantment    <0  0   1   2   3   4   5   6  >=7
	Chance of destruction  0%  0% 14% 29% 43% 57% 71% 86% 100%
