unicorn horn
	The unicorn horn, sometimes called a unihorn, is a weapon-tool.

	Unicorn horns are not randomly generated and can only be obtained
	by killing a unicorn, which leaves an uncursed +0 unicorn horn
	behind if killed in a way that leaves a corpse. Horns obtained
	from normal unicorns are considered magical items. Revived or
	polymorphed unicorns only have a 50% chance of leaving one upon
	death; the rest of the time, its horn will crumble to dust.

	As a weapon, the unicorn horn has a dedicated weapon skill which
	only it uses.

	As a tool, applying a noncursed unicorn horn can cure multiple
	negative status properties:	Blindness (non-physical),Deafness,
	Confusion, Hallucination, Stunning, Sickness, Nausea

	A unicorn horn cannot cure: Stoning, Sliming, Lycanthropy, Wounded
	legs, Amnesia, Fear

	Applying an uncursed unicorn horn will fix (d(2d2) - 1) ailments,
	whilst a blessed one can heal (d(2d4) - 1) ailments. A cursed
	unicorn horn will instead cause one or more of the applicable
	ailments listed above. If you are wearing a ring of sustain
	ability, a unicorn horn will not affect your attributes. When used
	by an intelligent monster with hands, noncursed unicorn horns are
	guaranteed to work on the first try; monsters will not use cursed
	unicorn horns.

	Dipping a noncursed unicorn horn into certain potions can "cure"
	them as well: dipping one into a potion of sickness changes it to
	a potion of fruit juice, and dipping one into a potion of
	blindness, confusion, or hallucination will turn it into a potion
	of water.

	Unicorns can use their own horn, as can a player polymorphed into
	a unicorn via the #monster; these produce the same effect as
	applying an uncursed unicorn horn.

	Note: Unicorn horns can no longer restore reduced attributes.
	Alternatives include potions of restore ability, the restore
	ability spell, prayer, or gain ability.

	Cursed unicorn horns also no longer reduce attributes. Instead,
	they can induce nausea; currently, this gives no message.
